commit.message:
bar: do not create an empty block 'foo'

The current code was creating an empty block to simplify the addition
of new blocks from the config callback. This resulted in an empty
'foo' block being created which is confusing to others.

Do not create this empty block anymore since the config callback now
assigns bar->blocks if there is no block created yet.

Refs #411

bar: do not assume existing blocks from the config

The current bar code assumes that at least one block is pointed to
by bar->blocks.

Do not assume that and assign bar->blocks from the config callback
if there is no block created yet.

config: make the callback map constant

It is a better practice to have a symmetric behavior within the config
code, creating and destroying the map passed to the callback itself. To
enforce this behavior, define the callback map argument as const.

bar: do not destroy map on config callback

It is inconsistent to have an assymetric behavior with the config
code creating the map and the caller to destroy it in its callback.

Do not destroy the config map from the bar code.

sys: do not include libgen.h

The libgen.h header was used within the config code and was included
there, there is no need to include it in the sys.h header, remove it.

config: include libgen.h

Include the libgen.h header for the POSIX version of dirname.

docs: mention Sway

Simplify the program description and mention Sway as it may not
be obvious that the software works out of the box with the Wayland
compositor as it is a drop-in replacement for i3.

docs: output must be newline terminated

Mention that the block output must be newline terminated as of i3blocks
1.5 and add an entry to the FAQ to cover this issue.

Refs #393

block: free conditionally

The block_destroy function destroys maps and frees the block
unconditionally, but this function may be called at any stages of
the block_create function, before maps are created. Test before free.

sys: use pid_t for waitpid return value

the waitpid syscall returns a pid_t, not a int.

Makefile.am: fix bash-completion dependency

Target `install-data-local` might be made before bashcompletion is
ready. This change fix it.

[vivien: reword commit message]
Fixes: #402
Closes: #457

i3blocks is a feed generator for text based status bars

Provide this better description of what the program is meant to be
in the README and the man page.

i3blocks.1: remove configuration section

The man page is meant to describe the usage of the i3blocks binary,
not the syntax of the configuration file which is already detailed in
the README, and consequently on the website. Remove the configuration
section and redirect the user to the website.

add a minimal system-wide configuration file

In order not to have an empty bar on a fresh installation of i3blocks,
include a basic system-wide configuration to fallback to. It can be
overriden by package maintainers for sure.

Note that it must not bring any dependency to the i3blocks package,
that is not what it is meant for.

Refs #230

readme: mention systemd usage

Mention the usage of systemd-cat for development and journalctl to
read i3blocks' output.

readme: the project does not include scripts anymore

Mention that this repository does not include the scripts anymore,
as this may not be obvious to a new user.

readme: repeat interval does not support clicks

Mention in the README (and thus the website) that the repeat interval
does not support the clicks, since such scripts are unlikely to read
their stdin and even if they do, it will still be racy because of the
reap and respawn time. Killing and restarting the commands isn't an
option either, since they may have an heavy initialization time and
that won't avoid the raciness anyway.

Refs #382
Makefile.am: install the man page

Makefile.am: fix SYSCONFDIR macro

After moving to an autotools based build, the SYSCONFDIR macro wasn't
defined anymore. Add it to DEFS to forward it to the source code.

Remove leading underscores from include guards

Include guards prefixed with underscore may not be compliant to the
C standard and may result in undefined behavior.

Fixes #372
build: dump version to 1.5
bump copyright years
i3blocks: add support for bash completion script

readme: add Void Linux to the list of distros

Add Void Linux to the list of distros that package i3blocks.

readme: add fedora to the list of distros

Add the link the to Fedora COPR package in the list of distros
packaging i3blocks.

readme: fix install-ed- typo

Fix the typo "installed" -> "install".

readme: fix written of -> on typo

Fix a "written of" instead of "written on" typo.

docs: rebuild documentation

Run rake to update the documentation.

block: remove unused variable err

The variable err is unused in functions block_send and block_setup.

block: define signal as an int

The signal member of the block structure is currently defined as
unsigned, while in C, signal numbers are defined as int.

This commit fixes the definition in block.h.
